The Agbado Police Station Area Command in Ifo Local Government, Ogun State has been given kudos by the landlords and other residents in the area. They said since the resumption of a new Divisional Police Officer, Superintendent of Police, SP Adekunle Awoniyi and his team the security situation has been relatively improved. Speaking to the reporter during the assessment of security situation and after the town hall meeting held at Agbado Crossing recently, Chief Delano Makanjuola, and Alhaji Muraina Balogun who jointly spoke on behalf of other members however showered praises on SP Adekunle Awoniyi over new development on security. The duo also added that the periodical meeting with the landlords and residents of the area has allowed the people to sleep with their two eyes closed. They, however, enjoined the community at large to expose and report people with suspicious movements in the area to the Police Command.